        Leafwhisper's leaves rustled — pleased by the question.
        Leafwhisper said,
        "Complementary skillsets! I handle communication and information sharing — Rootwalker manages terrain and practical navigation — together we cover all traveler needs very effectively, been working as a team for many cycles now and honestly I think the contrast helps, travelers who want conversation get that from me, travelers who prefer quiet get that from Rootwalker—"

        Rootwalker confirmed from across the shelter.
        "Works."

        One word — complete agreement.

        I smile despite my exhaustion.

        Buddy advised,
        "Get some sleep — your body needs recovery time for muscle repair and energy restoration."

        Leafwhisper agreed,
        "Buddy's absolutely right! Rest is crucial for multi-day journeys — we'll maintain this pattern for three days total before reaching the territorial boundary—"

        I am already lying down.

        Scout curls up beside me. Rootwalker settles near the entrance — silent guardian. Leafwhisper's leaves rustle softly, finally quieting — twenty-three kilometers — day one complete.

        I close my eyes.

        ¶

        I'd walked twenty-three kilometers through an alien forest with enthusiastic plant guides and survived.

        Tomorrow I'll do it again.

        But tomorrow is tomorrow.

        Tonight, I sleep.
      </text>
